# Web Interface — Interactions

Based on [Vercel Web Interface Guidelines](https://vercel.com/design/guidelines). Performance: `react-performance.mdc`. Next.js: use `next/link` for in-app navigation (MCP `/docs/app/getting-started/linking-and-navigating`).

## Keyboard & focus

- Full keyboard support per [WAI-ARIA APG](https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/)
- Visible `:focus-visible` rings; trap/return focus in modals per APG
- Hit targets ≥24px (≥44px touch); expand invisible hit area when visual is smaller

## Forms & inputs

- Hydration-safe — no lost focus/value after SSR
- Never block paste; support password managers and 2FA OTP paste
- `autocomplete`, meaningful `name`, correct `type` / `inputmode`
- Inline errors beside fields; on submit, focus first error
- Enter submits single-line input; in `textarea`, Enter = newline, ⌘/Ctrl+Enter = submit
- Keep submit enabled until request starts; then disable + spinner + idempotency where needed
- Loading buttons keep their label; use `…` for in-progress copy (`Saving…`)
- Trim values; no dead zones on checkbox/radio — label + control share one target
- Mobile inputs: ≥16px font or proper viewport meta — never disable browser zoom

## Navigation & state

- **URL reflects UI state** (filters, tabs, pagination) — repo uses `nuqs` / compose filters where applicable
- Navigation uses `<Link>` / `<a>` — support Cmd/Ctrl/middle-click; not `<button>` for route changes
- Back/Forward restores scroll when using Next.js App Router navigation
- Confirm destructive actions or offer Undo
- Warn on unsaved changes before leaving

## Feedback & motion

- Polite `aria-live` for toasts and inline validation
- Optimistic UI only with rollback/Undo on failure
- Honor `prefers-reduced-motion`; animate `transform`/`opacity` only
- `overscroll-behavior: contain` in modals/drawers

## Anti-patterns

```tsx
// ❌ div + onClick for internal route
<div onClick={() => router.push('/items')}>Items</div>

// ❌ Block paste on OTP field
onPaste={(e) => e.preventDefault()}

// ✅ Link + accessible name
<Link href="/items">Items</Link>
```

